¹ The work done by Felix (970-1038), in the way of restoration of monastic lise, and of ecclesiastical architecture in general, appears to have had important and permanent results ; but all these Chapters belong to the history of the Abbey of St. Gildas de Ruys, not to the history of Gildas; for this reason, I have not attempted more than the translation. One point, however, it will be well to notice. On p. 317 the close intercourse between Fleury and Brittany is mentioned as a reason why Breton, and probably British, documents have been preserved at the monastery of Fleury. In this part, that intercourse, in the person of Felix, is vividly pictured for us by a contemporary.
